## 6 minvol    vol         0.0120  0.0133  0.0146
calculate_portfolio_se <- function(results_df) {
  results_df %>%
    filter(complete.cases(mean_return, vol, sharpe)) %>%
    group_by(portfolio) %>%
    summarise(
      across(c(mean_return, vol, sharpe),
             list(mean = ~mean(.x, na.rm = TRUE), se = ~sd(.x, na.rm = TRUE))),
      n_sim_valid = n(),
      .groups = "drop"
    ) %>%
    rename_with(~gsub("_mean", "_avg", .x), contains("_mean"))
}

  # Reshape Gaussian results
  results_long_gauss <- results_gauss %>%
    dplyr::select(portfolio, mean_return, vol, sharpe) %>%
    dplyr::filter(complete.cases(mean_return, vol, sharpe)) %>%
    tidyr::pivot_longer(cols = c(mean_return, vol, sharpe),
                        names_to = "metric",
                        values_to = "value") %>%
    dplyr::mutate(metric = factor(metric, levels = c("mean_return", "vol", "sharpe"),
                                  labels = c("Mean Return", "Volatility", "Sharpe Ratio")))
  
  if (nrow(results_long_gauss) > 0) {
    # Density Plots (Gaussian) 
    plot_title_density_g <- "Distribution of Performance Metrics (d=50, Gaussian Model)"
    plot_subtitle_density_g <- paste("Based on", B_sim, "simulations. Dashed lines are original point estimates.")
    
    med_gauss <- results_long_gauss %>%                # already long format
    dplyr::group_by(portfolio, metric) %>%           # both facets
    dplyr::summarise(med = median(value, na.rm = TRUE),
                   .groups = "drop")

    # Density plot + dotted median line 
    p1_g <- ggplot(results_long_gauss, aes(x = value, fill = portfolio)) +
      geom_density(alpha = 0.6) +
      facet_wrap(~ metric, scales = "free") +
      
      geom_vline(data = med_gauss,                       
                 aes(xintercept = med, colour = portfolio),
                 linetype = "dotted", size = 1,
                 inherit.aes = FALSE) +
      
      scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1",
                        name = "Portfolio (Simulated)") +
      scale_colour_brewer(palette = "Set1", guide = "none") +  
      labs(title    = plot_title_density_g,
           subtitle = plot_subtitle_density_g,
           x = "Metric Value", y = "Density") +
      theme_minimal() +
      theme(legend.position = "bottom")
    
    print(p1_g)
    
    # Box Plots (Gaussian) 
    plot_title_boxplot_g <- "Comparison of Performance Distributions (d=50, Gaussian Model)"
    plot_subtitle_boxplot_g <- paste("Boxes show distribution over", B_sim, "simulations. Diamonds are original point estimates.")
    
    p3_g <- ggplot(results_long_gauss, aes(x = portfolio, y = value, fill = portfolio)) +
      geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.7, outlier.shape = NA) +
      facet_wrap(~ metric, scales = "free_y") +
      scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") +
      labs(title = plot_title_boxplot_g, subtitle = plot_subtitle_boxplot_g,
           x = "Portfolio Strategy", y = "Metric Value") +
      theme_minimal() +
      theme(legend.position = "none")
    print(p3_g)
    
  } else {
    warning("No valid Gaussian data remaining after filtering/pivoting for density/box plots.", call. = FALSE)
  } # End check for results_long_gauss
  
  
  # Scatter Plot (Gaussian) 
  plot_title_scatter_g <- "In-Sample Risk-Return Scatter Plot (d=50, Gaussian Model)"
  plot_subtitle_scatter_g <- paste("Cloud shows", B_sim, "simulations. Diamonds are original point estimates.")
  
  scatter_data_g <- results_gauss %>% filter(complete.cases(vol, mean_return))
  if(nrow(scatter_data_g) > 0) {
    p2_g <- ggplot(scatter_data_g, aes(x = vol, y = mean_return, color = portfolio)) +
      geom_point(alpha = 0.3, size = 1.5) + # Simulation cloud
      scale_color_brewer(palette = "Set1", name = "Portfolio Strategy") +
      labs(title = plot_title_scatter_g, subtitle = plot_subtitle_scatter_g,
           x = "In-Sample Volatility (Weekly)", y = "In-Sample Mean Return (Weekly)") +
      theme_minimal() +
      guides(color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(alpha = 1, size = 3)))
    print(p2_g)
  } 
  
}

2.4 Compare different resampling approaches

schemes   <- c("iid","block","gauss")
ports     <- c("minvol","maxdiv")
B         <- 200
block_len <- 20

results <- data.frame()
weight_store <- list()          
for (sc in schemes) {
  draw_fun <- switch(sc,
                     iid   = draw_iid,
                     block = function(R) draw_block_rows(R, l=block_len),
                     gauss = draw_gauss)
  for (pt in ports) {
    obj <- avg_and_store(rets, draw_fun, B, pt)
    w_bar <- obj$w_bar
    SR    <- sharpe(w_bar, rets)
    tag   <- paste(sc, pt, sep="_")
    weight_store[[tag]] <- obj$Wmat      
    results <- rbind(results,
                     data.frame(resample=sc, portfolio=pt, Sharpe=SR,
                                vol=sd(drop(rets %*% w_bar)),
                                mean=mean(drop(rets %*% w_bar))))
  }
}

ggplot(results, aes(resample, Sharpe, fill = resample)) +
  geom_col(width = .6, colour = "black") +
  facet_wrap(~ portfolio, nrow = 1) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1", guide = "none") +
  labs(title = "Sharpe ratio after resampling (sample covariance)",
       subtitle = paste0("Averaged over up to ", B,
                         " successful resamples â€” block length = ", block_len),
       x = "Resampling scheme", y = "Realised Sharpe on original data") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 13)

w_long <- purrr::imap_dfr(weight_store, ~
                            as.data.frame(.x) |>
                            pivot_longer(everything(), values_to="w") |>
                            mutate(tag=.y))
ggplot(w_long, aes(tag, w, fill=tag)) +
  geom_violin(trim=FALSE, alpha=.6) +
  labs(title="Weight dispersion across resamples",
       x="", y="Weight") +
  theme_minimal(base_size=12) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=45,hjust=1),
        legend.position="none")
